section.section:
The regulations for a home-based hospice care program shall require:
The medical director to be a physician licensed to practice medicine in this State;
The provision of bereavement services;
The provision of services to meet the spiritual or social needs of dying individuals and their families;
The provision of palliative and supportive medical, nursing, and other health services:
Directly or by contract for a general licensee; or
By referral only for a limited licensee;
Submission of an annual report which includes service utilization statistics in the format prescribed;
Written transfer agreements to provide acute inpatient care as needed; and
Minimum standards concerning the training and role of volunteers in a hospice care program.
